									Source code Management Tool: (Version control tool)
									===========================
SCM : to manage code 
====
Tracking information like modification of code, who and when created 

SVN -- sub version
Git-- local repo
Git-Hub -- centrol repo
Bit-bucket --
Gerrit --
TFS --

GIT:
====
3 phases
=========
1. workspace --- new file --untracked files(RED)  --- touch file name
	git status
2. staging/index area --- changes to be commited(GREEN) -- git add file name
	git status
3. local repository --- git commit -m "label" 
	git status
    git log -- local repo files 
	git show cid --(cid -- 7 char or full )


config GIT:
------------
git config --global user.name "raki"
git config --global user.email "vishnuvalasa@gmail.com"

remove(unset) GIT config:
-------------------------
git config --global --unset user.name
git config --global --unset user.email
 
git cmds:

	touch vvr1 -- WORKSPACE
	git status 
	git add vvr1 -- STAGE/INDEX
	git status 
	git commit -m "label" vvr1 -- LOCAL REPOSIT
	git status
	git log 
	git show cid 
	
** single commit for multiple files **

	touch vvr3 vvr4 vvr5
	git status 
	git add . or * or -A or vvr3 vvr4 vvr5
	git status 
	git commit -m "3rd label" 
	git status 
	git log
	git show cid

** either we can connect 1 or all files **






	
